com.maxmind.geoip2.model

Class CountryLookup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxmind.geoip2.model.CountryLookup
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CityLookup

    public class CountryLookup
extends Object
    This class provides a model for the data returned by the GeoIP2 Country end point. The only difference between the City, City/ISP/Org, and Omni model classes is which fields in each record may be populated.
    See Also:
    GeoIP2 Web Services

        public Country getCountry()

      • getMaxMind

      • getRegisteredCountry

        public Country getRegisteredCountry()
        Returns:
        Registered country record for the requested IP address. This record represents the country where the ISP has registered a given IP block in and may differ from the user's country.

      • getRepresentedCountry

        public RepresentedCountry getRepresentedCountry()
        Returns:
        Represented country record for the requested IP address. The represented country is used for things like military bases or embassies. It is only present when the represented country differs from the country.
